{"cursor":"3772","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox musical artist |name = Mark Jansen |background = solo_singer |image =\nMark Jansen (Epica) at Tuska 2006.jpg|thumb|250px |caption = Mark Jansen at\nTuska 2006 |birth_name = |birth_date = |Death = |genre = Symphonic metal,\nprogressive metal, death metal |occupation = Musician, songwriter |years_active\n= |instrument = Guitar, vocals, keyboards |First_album = |Latest_album =\n|Notable_albums = |Notable songs = |label = Nuclear Blast |associated_acts =\nEpica, MaYaN, After Forever |website = }} 'Mark Jansen', (born 15 December\n1978), is a heavy metal musician.\n\nAs guitarist, Jansen founded After Forever with Sander Gommans, and was one of\nthe main songwriters since their debut album [[Prison of Desire]]. He left After\nForever in 2002, http://www.faceculture.tv/index.php?cnti_key=11736877\nand after his departure the band took a new musical direction. Mark Jansen\nstarted a new symphonic metal band called Sahara Dust, which was later renamed\nEpica. His girlfriend at the time, Simone Simons, joined the band in 2003. In\nboth After Forever and Epica, Mark has performed growled vocals, complementing\nthe vocals of, respectively, Floor Jansen and Simone Simons. In 2010 Mark\nannounced that he has formed another band called MaYaN. Unlike his other bands,\nJansen sings in MaYaN but does not play guitar. The band released their debut\nalbum Quarterpast in spring 2011. http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseac-\ntion=blog.view&friendId=545273191&blogId=539158290\n","linknr":237,"url":"Mark_Jansen","recorded":1364223949,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Mark_Jansen&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Mark_Jansen&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikiped